[The black-faced spoonbill (_Platalea minor_) is a species in the ibis and spoonbill family, Threskiornithidae. Confined to the coastal areas of eastern Asia, it is the only spoonbill species regarded as endangered. For a picture, see https://cdn.download.ams.birds.cornell.edu/api/v1/asset/431876931/. - Mod.PMB

